272
00:13:59,618 --> 00:14:01,418
Time is of the "es-sance."

273
00:14:04,769 --> 00:14:05,635
Yes, sir.

274
00:14:06,088 --> 00:14:08,346
Yes, sir, I understand.
We'll let 'em know right away, sir.

275
00:14:08,843 --> 00:14:10,156
Over here, Shawn.

276
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:14,102
Dude, this is kind of exciting.
What's behind there?

277
00:14:15,543 --> 00:14:17,031
- That says "exit".
- I know.

278
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:19,441
We are completely making fools
of ourselves inside there.

279
00:14:19,610 --> 00:14:21,400
We need to cut our losses
and go home.

280
00:14:21,784 --> 00:14:23,410
This slump of yours
is out of control.

281
00:14:23,535 --> 00:14:25,555
I admit we're having
some early trouble,

282
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:28,037
but that room is
like kryptonite to my skills.

283
00:14:28,162 --> 00:14:31,369
It's, like, neutralizing my weapons.
I need to see thingsand touch stuff.

284
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:33,814
Has it ever occurred to you
that these are the kind of people

285
00:14:33,939 --> 00:14:36,351
that could figure out
you're not who you say you are?

286
00:14:36,476 --> 00:14:38,835
- Come on, son.
- Do not do Ed Lover on me.

287
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:41,505
We need to wow them with ideas
and we're right back in business.

288
00:14:41,674 --> 00:14:43,548
Or completely out of business.

289
00:14:45,468 --> 00:14:47,844
If we're gonna stay here,
you need to call your dad.

290
00:14:48,470 --> 00:14:51,014
- Since when do I need his help?
- You called him to get here.

291
00:14:51,182 --> 00:14:52,724
Which we didn't use.

292
00:14:54,102 --> 00:14:56,318
I may not be a planner,
or a detail man,

293
00:14:56,443 --> 00:14:59,764
or a taxpayer,
but when push comes to shove, I work,

294
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:01,690
- and I get the job done.
- My gosh.

295
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:04,466
Now follow me back in there,
and let's blow these guys' minds,

296
00:15:04,591 --> 00:15:05,841
scanners-style.

297
00:15:08,783 --> 00:15:12,593
We chose this hotel specifically because
none of the surrounding buildings

298
00:15:12,718 --> 00:15:14,545
are higher than two stories,

299
00:15:15,014 --> 00:15:17,716
so if we surround him
with all six bodyguards,

300
00:15:17,841 --> 00:15:21,586
then we have seemingly eliminated
all possibilities of an attack.

301
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:24,047
- So what are we missing?
- Here comes the wow.

302
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:28,333
- Yes, Mr. Spencer, you have something?
- As a matter of fact, I do, Walt.

303
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:31,555
If the assassin is unable
to take a shot from above,

304
00:15:31,742 --> 00:15:34,407
then I think there is a very,
very good possibility

305
00:15:34,532 --> 00:15:36,268
that he will shoot from beneath.

306
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:39,585
- From beneath?
- Indeed. Shoot from beneath.

307
00:15:40,106 --> 00:15:42,621
So, what are you saying,
the killer's like a groundhog,

308
00:15:42,746 --> 00:15:45,443
who digs little tunnels in the earth,
something like that?

309
00:15:46,087 --> 00:15:49,531
- What are you calculating, Alan?
- The odds of Mr. Spencer getting fired.

310
00:15:49,776 --> 00:15:50,651
What?

311
00:15:50,776 --> 00:15:54,243
I think that's about enough for today.
Let's meet tomorrow, 8:00 sharp.

312
00:15:55,284 --> 00:15:57,087
I was just gettin' warmed up, man.

313
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:07,344
It's really scraping the bottom
of the barrel, asking Lassie for help.

314
00:16:07,469 --> 00:16:10,113
Your ability to know nothing
about real police work

315
00:16:10,238 --> 00:16:12,035
has finally caught up to you.

316
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:14,236
- We can always just...
- We're not calling my dad.

317
00:16:14,361 --> 00:16:16,061
I can do this by myself.

318
00:16:17,014 --> 00:16:18,864
Exactly how does that work?

319
00:16:19,344 --> 00:16:21,722
- Whatever do you mean, chief?
- With your father.

320
00:16:21,847 --> 00:16:23,722
See, I saw him at the pizza place.

321
00:16:23,847 --> 00:16:24,997
You sure did.

322
00:16:25,299 --> 00:16:28,549
You see, he missed most
of my baseball games as a kid,

323
00:16:28,695 --> 00:16:32,699
and recently, he has been trying
to show me more support in my ventures.

324
00:16:40,349 --> 00:16:42,286
This is big boy work,
so what do you want?

325
00:16:42,461 --> 00:16:45,045
Quick question, more of a trivia thing.
Kind of a "what if".

326
00:16:45,213 --> 00:16:47,063
- Get to it.
- Have you ever given any thought

327
00:16:47,188 --> 00:16:49,702
to how or when someone would try
to assassinate Ashton Bonaventure?

328
00:16:49,827 --> 00:16:52,594
Don't spout out everything Tom Cruise
did in <i>Valkyrie</i>, I already pitched that.

329
00:16:52,834 --> 00:16:53,934
Bonaventure?

330
00:16:54,270 --> 00:16:57,691
- You're working for Bonaventure?
- Us and some other experts.

331
00:16:58,184 --> 00:16:59,822
I've been trying
since forever to get

332
00:16:59,947 --> 00:17:01,982
on one of these private
security details.

333
00:17:02,107 --> 00:17:05,357
I wrote to Gerald Ford when I was a kid,
telling him I wanted to protect him,

334
00:17:06,061 --> 00:17:07,409
and that I loved him.

335
00:17:07,534 --> 00:17:10,528
This might be your lucky day,
'cause I'm thinking of letting you in.

336
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,696
- Throwing you a bone.
- I'm not going to help you.

337
00:17:12,821 --> 00:17:15,075
If they wanted my ideas
they could have asked me themselves.

338
00:17:15,297 --> 00:17:17,797
Gus has 100 large in his pocket.

339
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:19,454
Are you trying to bribe me?

340
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:22,290
Fair enough. You drive a hard bargain.
And 3 bucks for a baby nugget?

341
00:17:22,802 --> 00:17:25,251
This is ridiculous! I know everything
there is about Bonaventure.

342
00:17:25,484 --> 00:17:28,423
I've been dealing with his people
for weeks, coordinating crowd control.

343
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:30,748
I would have been a real asset
in that room.

344
00:17:31,111 --> 00:17:32,717
I'm gonna call Bill McGoldrick.

345
00:17:33,924 --> 00:17:36,471
- Who?
- He's head of security. He hate me.

346
00:17:36,673 --> 00:17:39,265
I don't know him.
We've been dealing with Walter Snowden.

347
00:17:39,675 --> 00:17:41,301
- Who's that?
- Walter Snowden?

348
00:17:41,426 --> 00:17:44,145
- Head of Snowden security?
- I've never heard of Snowden security.

349
00:17:44,314 --> 00:17:45,688
You don't know Walter Snowden?

350
00:17:46,054 --> 00:17:49,904
I've never heard of Walter Snowden
or Snowden security in my life.

351
00:17:50,804 --> 00:17:51,804
Who is he?

352
00:17:54,949 --> 00:17:58,367
<i>Perhaps we should hear the rest
from Mr. Bonaventure himself.</i>

353
00:17:59,806 --> 00:18:00,786
<i>Just know...</i>

354
00:18:02,432 --> 00:18:04,596
He's the head of Bonaventure...

355
00:18:05,433 --> 00:18:07,739
Head of think tank operations.

356
00:18:09,182 --> 00:18:10,182
Crap.

357
00:18:17,213 --> 00:18:18,213
Crap.

358
00:18:19,770 --> 00:18:22,120
Now I gotta get a warrant
to get in this place.

359
00:18:31,915 --> 00:18:33,064
What the hell?

360
00:18:42,915 --> 00:18:43,915
Damn.

361
00:18:45,873 --> 00:18:46,873
Skittles?

362
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:49,697
Bonaventure
has never heard of Snowden.

363
00:18:49,822 --> 00:18:51,209
I don't get it.

364
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:53,840
We saw him on video.

365
00:18:55,155 --> 00:18:56,676
- Video was fake, Gus.
- Fake?

366
00:18:57,053 --> 00:18:59,596
<i>Hello, team.
Thank you for participating.</i>

367
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:01,556
It was footage of Bonaventure

368
00:19:01,727 --> 00:19:04,058
at a golf tournament
or sales convention or something.

369
00:19:04,468 --> 00:19:06,344
No, should have known better.

370
00:19:06,469 --> 00:19:08,521
He would have loved
my pillow comb idea.

371
00:19:09,595 --> 00:19:11,246
Snowden tried to kill him
in the past,

372
00:19:11,371 --> 00:19:13,359
but he could never crack
Bonaventure's security.

373
00:19:13,838 --> 00:19:17,196
<i>If a bad guy can do it, I want us
to have considered it beforehand.</i>

374
00:19:18,299 --> 00:19:21,223
He puts together this think tank
to gather as many ideas as possible

375
00:19:21,348 --> 00:19:23,202
so that he can carry out the hit
successfully.

376
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:26,039
There's no record
of a Walter Snowden in our database.

377
00:19:26,474 --> 00:19:28,805
- What about the others?
- Boyd, Progoyovic, and Zenuk

378
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:30,788
all check out.
We will question them.

379
00:19:30,913 --> 00:19:33,367
So let me get this straight.
You joined this organization,

380
00:19:33,492 --> 00:19:35,256
didn't bother to check
if they were legit,

381
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:37,977
and then you gave 'em ideas
about how to kill one of your idols?

382
00:19:38,178 --> 00:19:40,260
If it's any consolation,
all of his ideas stank.

383
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:41,473
- Stunk.
- Stank.

384
00:19:41,598 --> 00:19:43,097
- Stinkeded?
- I'm sure they did.

385
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:45,635
I won't say that I'm not gonna hold this
over your head forever,

386
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,393
because, honestly, of course I am.

387
00:19:47,561 --> 00:19:50,853
It's not the time to gloat 'cause you're
right for the first time in your life.

388
00:19:51,024 --> 00:19:52,417
I'm just having a mini slump.

389
00:19:52,542 --> 00:19:55,860
The important thing is, I need evidence
bags for the rest of those Skittles.

390
00:19:56,543 --> 00:19:58,363
We have four days to find this guy.

391
00:19:58,731 --> 00:20:01,199
- Why four days?
- That's when Bonaventure gets to town.

392
00:20:01,754 --> 00:20:03,535
Bonaventure's flight got
in four hours ago.

393
00:20:03,734 --> 00:20:06,634
- He's already at his hotel.
- Hopefully alive.

394
00:20:10,459 --> 00:20:12,483
What is the meaning
of this interruption?

395
00:20:14,431 --> 00:20:16,719
I believe
that you will be in grave danger,

396
00:20:16,844 --> 00:20:19,968
and believe that there will be
an attempt made on your life.

397
00:20:20,611 --> 00:20:23,137
- And how do you know that?
- Because I am a psychic.

398
00:20:23,488 --> 00:20:24,538
I'm also...

399
00:20:25,550 --> 00:20:27,934
An inventor. It's a pillow that combs
your hair while you sleep.

400
00:20:28,611 --> 00:20:29,561
Check it out.

401
00:20:29,729 --> 00:20:32,772
You need to cancel your speech tonight,
and we need to get you out of town.

402
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:35,233
No, this is the most important
appearance of the year for me.

403
00:20:35,429 --> 00:20:39,153
12 other companies are trying
to launch what I'm going to announce.

404
00:20:39,322 --> 00:20:41,322
If we don't go first,
we're finished.

405
00:20:41,491 --> 00:20:43,866
Five years of development.
I'm going on.

406
00:20:44,303 --> 00:20:45,618
My company depends on it.

407
00:20:45,806 --> 00:20:47,555
No, sir, your attackers
depend on it.

408
00:20:48,122 --> 00:20:50,665
I pay these people
very well to keep me safe,

409
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:53,585
and nothing in this world is gonna
stop me from making that speech.

410
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:55,215
Right now, you're not safe,

411
00:20:55,340 --> 00:20:57,936
and this guy, who has solved
over 50 unsolvable cases,

412
00:20:58,061 --> 00:20:59,495
is your best chance to live.

413
00:20:59,620 --> 00:21:02,176
- And why is that?
- Because solving these unsolvable cases

414
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:05,680
is usually impressive to people,
and because I spent the last 12 hours

415
00:21:05,848 --> 00:21:07,491
with your would-be assassin,

416
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:10,560
and I know every single little thing
that he might try.

417
00:21:13,311 --> 00:21:15,661
All right, psychic,
here's your shot.

418
00:21:16,313 --> 00:21:17,734
I'm going to my car.

419
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,012
Get me there.

420
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:28,994
<i>I've even seen tiny plastique explosives
in cell phones.</i>

421
00:21:32,317 --> 00:21:34,065
Don't answer that.
That stays where it is.

422
00:21:34,190 --> 00:21:36,186
In fact, everybody, cell phones out.
Let's see 'em.

423
00:21:36,311 --> 00:21:38,061
Now put 'em on the floor.

424
00:21:39,632 --> 00:21:40,682
Let's move.

425
00:21:47,723 --> 00:21:50,975
<i>Generally people are programmed to find
persons in uniform less suspicious.</i>

426
00:21:51,871 --> 00:21:52,685
The maid.

427
00:21:53,071 --> 00:21:54,071
The maid!

428
00:22:03,065 --> 00:22:03,988
Axe for men?

429
00:22:04,260 --> 00:22:05,264
What?

430
00:22:06,015 --> 00:22:07,115
She's clean.

431
00:22:14,478 --> 00:22:16,149
<i>Me? I carry a baby.</i>

432
00:22:16,827 --> 00:22:17,827
Baby.

433
00:22:17,952 --> 00:22:19,826
- The baby?
- The baby!

434
00:22:23,783 --> 00:22:25,533
Baby's real. She's clean.

435
00:22:27,577 --> 00:22:28,888
<i>I use skin contact.</i>

436
00:22:34,072 --> 00:22:36,312
Feel it, orchid man!
Nice try!

437
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,855
It's water. He's clean.

438
00:22:38,943 --> 00:22:39,816
He's clean.

439
00:22:49,063 --> 00:22:52,453
I think we can all agree
that that was a horrible mistake.

440
00:22:53,149 --> 00:22:55,449
Good job tackling that maid, though.

441
00:22:56,399 --> 00:22:59,544
I think the only thing to come out
of this exercise will be lawsuits.

442
00:23:00,335 --> 00:23:01,785
I'd call my lawyer,

443
00:23:02,186 --> 00:23:04,465
but I seem to have dropped my phone.

444
00:23:06,022 --> 00:23:07,022
Wait!

445
00:23:15,078 --> 00:23:16,428
Hair looks great.

446
00:23:19,839 --> 00:23:22,591
Chief, I really don't see the point
in getting upset over spilled milk.

447
00:23:22,716 --> 00:23:23,937
Why would I be upset?

448
00:23:24,062 --> 00:23:25,939
The most powerful businessman
in the state

449
00:23:26,064 --> 00:23:28,844
is the target of an assassination,
and one of my people helped plan it.

450
00:23:28,969 --> 00:23:31,528
- It was two. Gus was there as well.
- Why would you say that?

451
00:23:31,653 --> 00:23:33,866
It might help cushion the blow
if we distribute the blame.

452
00:23:33,991 --> 00:23:35,863
- Cushion who?
- I guess me mostly.

453
00:23:36,759 --> 00:23:38,525
Chief,
the man that we are looking for

454
00:23:38,650 --> 00:23:40,589
is operating
under the alias of "Walter Snowden".

455
00:23:40,714 --> 00:23:42,810
The remaining members
of the bogus think tank

456
00:23:42,935 --> 00:23:45,423
